Creamy Macaroni and Cheese

2 tbsp butter
1 c cottage cheese
2 c milk (not skim)
1 tsp dry mustard
pinch cayenne
pinch freshly grated nutmeg
1/4 tsp freshly ground black pepper
1 lb sharp or extra sharp cheddar, grated
1/2 lb elbow pasta, uncooked

Heat oven to 375F and position oven rack in upper 1/3 of oven. Use 1 tbsp butter to greas 9" round or square baking dish. In a blender, puree cottage cheese, milk, mustard, cayenne, nutmeg, and pepper together. Reserve 1/4 c grated cheese for topping. In a large bowl, combine remaining cheese, milk mixture, and uncooked pasta. Pour into prepared pan, cover tightly with foil and bake for 30 min. Uncover pan , stir gently, sprinkle with reserved cheese and dot with remaining butter. Bake, uncovered, 30 min more until browned. Let cool at least 15 min before serving.

Note: Combine everything and put in fridge in the morning, will cook in half the time.
